34, single, excited about the future, surrounded by incredible people who light up my soul, enjoying rich conversation, full of wonder and optimism, always see things glass half full and trying to sprinkle positivity, joy and childlike fun wherever I go and with whoever I meet 🥰

I love Christmas 🎄 I love the energy, the festivities, the lights, the songs … but this year it’s just very different. There’s been so much change this year and because of all of that I feel like I’ve just had to let go. 

My sister and I dream of having a white Christmas, celebrating with my kids and partner and lots of our family, playing fun board games, having really fulfilling conversation with people I love and of course eating lots of delicious food 🥰

We’ve sort of just decided that until then we would just made our own cute little ritual. So this year we watched Home Alone 1,2&3 😂 played lots of board games, went to church, sang carols around the house and spend the afternoon with my dads side of the family. 

It’s a time of year that I have deep empathy for those that are struggling, those that feel alone, those that don’t have support… and I send me heart out to everyone of you that need it 🤍

Merry Christmas Everyone 🎄

I absolutely loved training for the upcoming season of @sasaustralia It’s the first time since finishing my athletic career that I’ve dedicated myself to a physical and mental challenge... and I absolutely loved taping back into that resilient, determined, kick-ass version of myself. 

As my coach would always say “proper preparation prevents piss-poor performance” 🤣 For me, the most challenging part was not knowing what we would be doing…so I literally put myself through everything I could possibly think of. 
I thrive of knowing the end outcome, like how many reps, how long, how many rounds…but SAS is the complete opposite, so I knew I had to get comfortable with that uncertainty and the only way I would be confident in my ability is if I had done it before…so I trained my ass off for this … I was so frikken prepared thanks to the epic few people I had by my side, challenging me, pushing me & supporting me!!

Would you guys go on this show??? 
Not long now till it airs 😬

It’s been an incredibly tough week - I don’t have the words to articulate it all right now, but all I know is that this is the end of a very long, heavy and challenging cycle…and I’m excited to leave this cycle behind and start something new, taking only the lessons, wisdom and very few people to the other side.

Ohhh the pain of this photo still hurts to look at!
The week that followed my exit from @sasaustralia was some of the hardest yet. I felt so broken and defeated, but more of a spiritual defeat, a loss of hope and faith in my path forward and ability to see the light amongst all that darkness. I know it can seem like just a singular event, but at that time, it felt like so many things in my life were falling apart and this was just another thing that didn’t go my way.
When I make the decision to commit to something, I give my heart and soul to it. I’ve always been that way and I love that about myself as I never have regrets. It means the highs can be extremely high … but the lows can hit so fucking hard.
Looking back at these photos now hurts my little heart, but I’m equally so frikken proud of myself for giving it everything I had and more.
Here’s to a brighter future and a new found trust and faith in my path forward!!! And to anyone feeling how I did back then, struggling to stay positive and optimistic when your life around you feels like it’s falling apart…I see you, I feel you, I love you…feel it all, let it out and know you’re not alone…

p.s On the same day I dislocated my shoulder, I tore up my finger abseiling down the tower…clearly was not my day!!

Just wanted to say the biggest thank you to you all for the endless support and love you have shared with me over the past few weeks when I’ve really needed it. Reading your comments and messages truly brought a smile and warmth to my heart. 
People always talk about the negatives of social media, but this little community right here is filled with warmth and love and kindness…and I hope I can give you that same positive energy back through my posts too! I send you all so much love and happiness 🤍

Feeling so much better this week after being so low and sad the past few weeks. Gosh it hit me so hard and none of the usual “tools” I use to help me feel better like meditation, journaling, exercising or walking gave me any relief. It was pretty scary to be honest …
I think it was amplified by the eclipses, getting covid and watching my injury play out again on SAS. Sometimes we need to go through the big lows to clear out the trauma that had been lying dormant, to finally let it pass through so we can make space for something beautiful…at least that’s the perspective I take!!
Sending you all love, especially those who are struggling or are going through the heavy emotions…this too shall pass ✨
#mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #eclipse #sasaustralia

After I came back from SAS and my shoulder was slightly better, I decided I wanted to fully commit to a weights program and see if I could transform my body. I’ve always done weights but more functional weights with lots of HIIT and long hikes. So I asked @m.acefitness to create a program for me and help train me a few times a week. At first I couldn’t even put the plates on the barbell because my shoulder was so weak after dislocating it 🤦🏽‍♀️ but now that it’s almost 100% better I’m really enjoying weights training and I’m learning a lot. 
I also think it’s amazing how your body responds to different types of training…you really can shape your body however you want to by doing different styles of training and I think that’s so cool.

If you had of asked me during school or anytime after that if I would consider going to uni, you would have got a hard no from me. It was never something I felt I needed given my career hasn’t required it and the path I’ve chosen to peruse is sooooo different from the ‘societal norm’.
It’s interesting how your life takes so many twists and turns and sometimes you end up where you never thought you would … at least that’s what happened to me.
I love running my own business and working as an ambassador, in TV, in consulting … but the one thing all of those have in common is the uncertainly of when your next’ job’ will come in. And as I’ve gotten older, and had a significant amount of time being single and therefore financially supporting myself, the call to have financial security and consistency became more important to me. Plus I’ve encountered similar remarks of “we see the value of having your name attached to the project, but what would you actually be doing?”
Kind of frustrating to me that at this stage of my career I still need to validate my contribution 😏 but that frustration lead me to the decision to embark on my MBA (Master of Business Administration) with @uqbusiness and my gosh, I have been absolutely loving it. 
It has taught me so much about myself that I never could see through my other work and the challenge of completing it within 18month has created so much momentum and intensity that I feel like I’ve really progressed myself in 2023 far more that other years.
Anyway, I just wanted to share a little about it and possibly show you that it’s ok for your life to take many twists and turns…your always on the right path and you will always be led to where you’re meant to be…all in the right time. Trust it!
Procrastinating studying for my accounting exam … so here’s a reel I decided to make instead 😂🫠

A few BEFORE & AFTERS in Jordan for @sasaustralia!
I’ll let you guess which ones were which, although it shouldn’t be too difficult 😔 
I thought I’d also share some of the notes I made the night before we entered the course. They were basically all mental reminders, confirming to myself I was as ready as I’d ever be, that I’d done the physical and mental work and that this was all going to be a test of mental and emotional resilience. Words I think we can all benefit from reminding ourself of from time to time (let me know in the comments which one hit home most for you) 
And even though I wasn’t in the course long enough to test that mental & emotional resilience, the days that followed my departure were some of the toughest yet. Alone, in a hotel room, for 5 days, overwhelmed with sadness … 
But I’ll forever be grateful to the incredible @sasaustralia team, the docs @danpronk and Rhinata for taking care of me, and the amazing psychologist who helped me pick up the pieces and slowly put them back together again 🫶🏽🤍 thank you 🙏🏽
I’ll be all smiles tomorrow after this Accounting exams over

Post exam celebration 🤍 so glad that subjects over, accounting was tough!! That’s 8 down 4 to go then your girl graduates 👩🏽‍🎓 … who would have thought. Also this room looks bare as cause I’m moving so everything feels a bit all over the place and uni took up all my energy. Now that it’s done, time to pack 🙏🏽

Truly grateful to be entering 2024 with a continued partnership with @lshautoaus 🙏🏽 It has been an honour to work with this team for 5 years now, meeting so many wonderful customers and attending their fantastic events … @lshautoaus really do create the most incredible customer experiences.
Thank you for the privilege of representing your brand and organisation in a public capacity, I know that decision is never made lightly. I’m so excited about what 2024 will bring and I hope I get to meet more of you through this journey 🤍

Currently packing up my apartment, preparing to move out. Having spent a lot of my live moving from place to place, it has honestly been such a saving grace to have grounded into one place for the past two years. I’m forever grateful for this safe space God provided me to do some deep deep healing over that time and now I feel really ready to move on and start a new journey. 
I really hope everyone has a chance to feel that grounded stability in a home. I know it’s not always the case, but as a woman who has been single for a few years, it has been such a blessing to have this a sanctuary when I feel safe, relaxed and at peace…that’s what a home should feel like, so I pray you all have that 🫶🏽

Last few days in my place before I walk into a new and exciting season of my life… and I’ve got to say, I feel excited, ready and calm 🙏🏽
I feel called to share a bit more of my life with you guys on here which is new for me as I’ve always had a little battle with social media internally…but the past month has showed me how much support and love there is here and how helpful it can be to share and connect more deeply online with people I may never know in person. So thank you for creating that safe space with me!! When I’m ready, I’ll post about this new adventure I’m embarking on … for now, have a wonderful, love-filled weekend 🫶🏽

Oooffftttt - woke up this morning with such anxiety! So much going on, so much change, so many practical steps that need to fall into place and such limited time to do it.
So I spent some time in prayer this morning, just asking for help, guidance and some super natural blessings to assist me with this all of this change and for the process to be smooth, easy and enjoyable. I don’t know about you guys, but moving and change is obviously a bit stressful - I think for me, it’s the fear of the unknowns that catch me out…so I’m just trying to take it one step at a time, make a list off all the things I need to action and ask for help where possible🙏🏽
Could really go for another nature walk right now to flush out some of these unsteady feelings 🍃

Such a fun day yesterday at the @pgaofaustralia with my bestie @_nesskate
Gosh I am going to miss you 😢 …
An epic few days enjoying the @pgaofaustralia and soaking up all the incredible dining experience @visitbrisbane and @queensland have to offer 🙌🏽

The past few months have been a rollercoaster of emotions, which have brought about so many wonderful changes which I’m excited to share with you as I start this new journey in Dubai. 
I’m sure you all have a lot of questions about this move and trust that I will share it with you in due course. At this stage I have no set plans yet in Dubai which is a little scary, I just knew I needed to follow this calling from deep within. 
Moving overseas has been something I have felt called to for so long, it just was never quite the right time…but now the time has come! I want to share this journey with you in hopes it inspires you to honour your own inner-callings and to have faith in the path ahead, even if you don’t yet know what it’s going to look like right now…cause I sure don’t!! I guess that’s life though right…just taking one step at a time and trusting that you will always know what to do next when you get there.

A new journey begins … 
My emotions are flying all over the place 😂 I go from excitement to worry to what ifs, but I keep hearing in prayer “one step at a time” so I’m leaning into that.
Gosh you guys are amazing and so full of love 🫶🏽 thank you so so much for your enduring support, it means so much to me. I want to share more and connect more, so I’d love for you to share with me the things you’d like to hear or see more of… any help you can give to help me discern  what to share would be so appreciated 🙌🏽

Found a home in Dubai 🫶🏽 
It was a stressful few days running around trying to find somewhere I felt comfortable, peaceful and safe, but I found it 🙏🏽
I’m so excited to move in tomorrow and unpack ALLL the things and get set up in a daily routine. Those daily rituals, like a morning coffee, gym, healthy breakfast, reading daily are so important to me. It grounds me in and brings me strength, peace, calmness, energy, focus…which I haven’t felt for a few weeks with the move, packing up life in Australia and uncertainty since landing.
Now that I have that step checked off I’m excited to see where God leads me next ❤️
Let’s see where this journey leads …

We’ve all been broken at some point, some more than others… but never let that dampen your ability to shine love out into the world and onto others 💛 I see the negative comments on my recent posts, but what I feel is the hurt that must be behind those comments … My commitment to God is a new walk for me, I have fears, I have doubts, I have concerns… but I also know that the way I was moving through life before is not how I want to go forward. This year has been incredibly challenging and at many times I’ve felt broken…but God has  given me the gift of His trust in me, His faith in me and His love for me. So to those struggling, stand strong, walk proud, you’ve come so far. Honour your journey, wounds and all…it’s made you into the beautiful soul you are today 🙏🏽

Social media has become a platform that is so heavily influenced by the enemy. Society places such value on external validation, like how many followers someone has, as if that’s the only factor that determines someone’s value. It really bothers me, because it sends a message, especially to young girls that they should aspire for fame, thinking that’s what will fill them up inside … but it never will.
It’s easy to look at someone on social media and think they have an amazing life, great relationship, success, money etc and that you can have that too if you just get a bit more famous or have a few more followers, which typically means you will compromise yourself to get it. But when you actually think about the people who inspire you, they generally have focused first on their craft, skill, career etc, which led them to fame…that was the case for me anyway. I always dreamed of being an Olympian and God knows I worked so hard for it, for year and years without any recognition to one day, overnight, become “famous”. 
So I pray instead that young girls focus on being healthy, building a career, having quality friendships, supporting others and lifting them up and hopefully also giving back. Those are the real fruits and blessings of God…and if you’re gifted a platform to influence others, please honour it, and use it for good!!
Thankful for all those closed door…because it led me here 🙏🏽

I never would have expected the year to end this way!! Giving my life to God, following His call to move my life to Dubai, meeting you on my first week at Church in Brisbane and spending our first Christmas together in New York 🥰 I can’t tell you how long I’ve waited for this … you just have to keep faith in His plan and in His timing ... God is so so good and I can’t wait to see what He has in store for 2024 ✝️
This White Christmas with you was more special than I could have imagined @survivetothrivenation ☃️🎄🥰

2024 … Showtime 🎥
Ready for a year of growth, of love, of sowing long-term seeds, of building for the future. A year full of adventure, joy, friendship and possibilities.
Praying your 2024 is full of miracles, unexpected blessings, love, peace, freedom and faith 🙏🏽

#2024 #christian #god #godisgood #faith

Two months ago I gave my life to God. The journey since then has been wild to say the least, but I wouldn’t have it any other way. 
Those few weeks before turning to God were my lowest yet. I can’t tell you how broken I was. Getting Covid, feeling defeated after getting injured in SAS and having to re-live that pain again as it aired in the public eye. Doing back to back media and breaking down in tears in the few moments between interviews. Trying to pick myself up but feeling so defeated. 
Don’t get me wrong, I’ve gone through tough times before…but this was different…it was a loss of faith, of hope, and feeling like no matter how hard I tried or how many personal development books I read or how much I tried to manifest, nothing good seemed to last. That’s when I knew I had to do something different and I had to surrender it all to God.

He saved me. He is putting all the pieces back together again in the most beautiful way. At times it’s painful, but I know it will be beautiful. God has already blessed my life so richly and I’m excited to see where He takes me next.
I pray that whoever needs to hear this, whoever resonates with this, that you know God is with you not matter what. He is calling you, He loves you, He wants to help you. That you are safe, that you can rest in Him and He will make things better. 
Sending my love and prayers to you all.
Thank you for supporting me and loving me along this journey. It means so much to me 🤍

#praisejesus #god #faith #mentalhealth #christian

To those of you who are in a season of waiting for love…please wait, please be patient. A relationship blessed by God is the only love you want. I know it can be tough to wait and you may be tempted to settle for short term fills… but be strong and be convicted that God WILL bless you. He has not forsaken you!! He knows your heart, He is faithful, and He will bring you the love you desire, all in His miraculous timing.

Our encounter was miraculous in so many ways, so I pray that God blesses you with a miraculous encounter of love too. I pray that He encourages you in your season of waiting and that any bonds or chains that have held you back from receiving love are broken right now. I pray that when you meet the person God has given to you that you will know in your spirit that this was His doing and therefore it has been blessed by God. 
Have faith … this is your sign love is near.
Here’s to many more years loving you darling, and many more nights in your arms 🙏🏽🤍
